This after six people were apprehended in Khayelitsha this week in connection with a mob attack in which two people were murdered. CAPE TOWN – Cape Town police are warning communities to not take the law into their own hands. This after six people were apprehended in Khayelitsha this week in connection with a mob attack in which two people were murdered. The victims had been accused of robbery. They were rounded up and set alight. The police's Andre Traut says: “The provincial commissioner of the Western Cape issued a stern warning to community members that [the] SAPS will not allow them to take the law into their own hands and said that crime can’t be handled by committing more crime.”